      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/36/48",
      "text": [
        " : سَأَلْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ رَجُلٍ ذَبَحَ فَسَبَقَهُ اَلسِّكِّينُ فَقَطَعَ اَلرَّأْسَ فَقَالَ \"ذَكَاةٌ وَحِيَّةٌ فَلاَ بَأْسَ بِأَكْلِهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4168 - Umar ibn Udhaynah narrated from Al-Fudayl who said: I asked Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as) about a man who was slaughtering an animal, and the knife moved too quickly and severed the head completely.\nImam (as) said: \"It is a valid slaughtering, and there is no harm in eating it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
